        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:24PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hammond, or 10 miles northwest of North Myrtle Beach Airport. This
thunderstorm was moving slowly east toward the coast.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph. Torrential rainfall is also
occurring with this storm and may lead to localized
flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hickory Grove and Hammond.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Do not
drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Continuous cloud to
ground lightning is occurring with this storm. Lightning is one of
nature's leading killers.</instruction>
